burnOptions(uint256,int24,int24).details: Will exercise if necessary, and will revert if user does not have enough collateral to exercise.

params.tickLimitHigh: Price slippage limit when burning an ITM option.
params.tickLimitLow: Price slippage limit when burning an ITM option.
params.tokenId: The tokenId of the option position to be burnt.

burnOptions(uint256[],int24,int24).details: Will exercise if necessary, and will revert if user does not have enough collateral to exercise.

params.positionIdList: The list of tokenIds for the option positions to be burnt.
params.tickLimitHigh: Price slippage limit when burning an ITM option.
params.tickLimitLow: Price slippage limit when burning an ITM option.

calculateAccumulatedFeesBatch(address,ui.details: Can be costly as it reads information from 2 ticks for each leg of each tokenId.

params.positionIdList: List of positions. Written as [tokenId1, tokenId2, ...].
params.user: Address of the user that owns the positions.

returns._2: balances A list of balances and pool utilization for each position, of the form [[tokenId0, balances0], [tokenId1, balances1], ...].
returns.premium0: Premium for token0 (negative = amount is owed).
returns.premium1: Premium for token1 (negative = amount is owed).

calculatePortfolioValue(address,int24,ui.details: The return values do not include the value of the accumulated fees.value0 and value1 are related to one another according to: value1 = value0 * price(atTick).

params.atTick: Tick at which the portfolio value is evaluated.
